---

# 📋 Features Explained

## 📌 Process Information

The application retrieves information from:

```
/proc/<pid>/status
```

Displays:

- Process Name
- Process ID (PID)
- Process State
- Number of Threads

Example

```
Name: firefox

Pid: 1256

State: Sleeping

Threads: 24
```

---

## 🧠 Memory Layout Inspection

The application reads

```
/proc/<pid>/maps
```

and extracts

- Start Address
- End Address
- Memory Size
- Permissions
- Section Type
- Region Description

Example

```
Address Start
Address End
Size (KB)
Permissions
Section Type
Details
```

---

# 🏷️ Memory Sections Identified

The inspector classifies memory regions into:

| Section | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| TEXT | Executable code segment |
| DATA | Read-write data segment |
| HEAP | Dynamic memory allocation |
| STACK | Function call stack |
| VDSO | Virtual Dynamic Shared Object |
| VVAR | Virtual Variables |
| OTHER | Unclassified memory region |
| Anonymous | Memory without a named mapping |

---

# 🔑 Memory Permissions

| Permission | Meaning |
|------------|---------|
| `r` | Read |
| `w` | Write |
| `x` | Execute |
| `p` | Private Mapping |
| `s` | Shared Mapping |

Example

```
r-xp
```

means

- Read
- Execute
- Private Mapping

