---

# 📈 Advantages

- Lightweight and fast
- Uses native Linux interfaces
- No external dependencies
- Easy to understand
- Useful for learning OS concepts
- Provides insight into process memory organization

---

# ⚠️ Limitations

- Linux-specific (depends on the `/proc` filesystem)
- Requires appropriate permissions to inspect some processes
- Read-only inspection (no memory modification)
- Console-based interface
- Limited to information exposed by the kernel

